vulnerability.name: USN-5904-2
vulnerability.description: USN-5904-1 fixed vulnerabilities in SoX. It was discovered that the fix for CVE-2021-33844 was incomplete. This update fixes the problem.  Original advisory details:   Helmut Grohne discovered that SoX incorrectly handled certain inputs. If a  user or an automated system were tricked into opening a specially crafted  input file, a remote attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a  denial of service. This issue only affected Ubuntu 14.04 ESM, Ubuntu 16.04 ESM,  and Ubuntu 18.04 LTS. (CVE-2019-13590)    Helmut Grohne discovered that SoX incorrectly handled certain inputs. If a  user or an automated system were tricked into opening a specially crafted  input file, a remote attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a  denial of service. (CVE-2021-23159, CVE-2021-23172, CVE-2021-23210,  CVE-2021-33844, CVE-2021-3643, CVE-2021-40426, CVE-2022-31650, and  CVE-2022-31651)

statements.status_notes: USN-5904-1 caused a minor regression in SoX.
